The paper deals with estimation and learning algorithms for dynamical systems, which are commonly studied in the fields of machine learning, control theory, and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers a broad range of topics related to learning algorithms and their applications. The paper also involves the analysis of bias and variance trade-offs, which is a common theme in statistical learning theory, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another likely category. The use of estimation algorithms and the incorporation of expert demonstrations suggest that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves experimental evaluations of the proposed methods, which may fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering).
